##Before the city was sealed off, where did more than five million people leave Wuhan? A new frontier

Hi, Monica and Monica

Function description, here is the "First Finance" magazine (predecessor "first finance weekly") readers club, we discover wonderful business value for you, also invited you to explore the bright business world.

On the evening of January 26, the Government of the People's Republic of China held a news conference on the prevention and control of pneumonia in COVID-19, and Wuhan Mayor Zhou Xianwang said that because of the Spring Festival and the impact of the epidemic, more than five million people have left Wuhan, and nine million remain in the city.

Where did those five million people go?

On January 23, the cities of Wuhan, Ezhou and Huanggang were closed to traffic, with public transport suspended in Red Cliff and Xiantao.

From 10:00 that morning, Wuhan City bus, subway, ferry, long-distance passenger transport suspended operations, airport, railway station from the Han Channel temporarily closed. From 11:20, all access to Ezhou's railway stations will be temporarily closed. From 1700 hours, all buses, ferries, and rural buses in Xiantao will be suspended, and all entertainment and indoor sports venues will be closed. From 2400 hours, Metro stations and railway stations leaving downtown Huanggang will be closed, public transport and long-distance passenger services will be suspended, and cinemas, Internet cafes and other indoor cultural and entertainment venues in downtown Huanggang will also be closed. Red Cliff City bus, rural passenger transport, provincial and county-level passenger transport suspended.

As an important hub city in China's railway passenger transport network, Wuhan has the north-south Artery beijing-guangzhou high-speed railway and east-west to Shanghai-han Lotus along the river railway. In 2019, Wuhan's high-speed rail system reached 152 cities, ranking just behind Beijing, Shanghai, Zhengzhou and Nanjing, according to the new first-tier Cities Research Institute of Finance and Economics. Wuhan's position as a hub in the civil aviation network is no better than that of high-speed rail, but Wuhan Tianhe Airport also handled 24.5 million passengers in 2018, ranking 16th in the country's ten-millionth airport.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
According to big data on migration from Baidu maps, between 60% and 70% of people who set off from Wuhan each day went to other cities in Hubei Province during the Spring Festival travel rush from January 10 to January 22, next are Henan Province, Hunan Province, Anhui Province, Chongqing City, Jiangxi Province. From the urban dimension, in addition to the cities of Hubei, the proportion of people from Wuhan to Xinyang, Chongqing, Changsha, Beijing, Shanghai and Zhengzhou is also high.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
In Hubei Province, Xiaogan and Huanggang are the two cities with the highest proportion of people returning from Wuhan, with an average of 13.03 per cent and 12.64 per cent leaving Wuhan for Xiaogan and Huanggang each day. As of 8:00 a.m. on January 27,2020, a total of 698 cases of pneumonia had been confirmed in Wuhan, 154 in Huanggang, 100 in Xiaogan, 90 in Jingmen and 63 in Xianning, according to the epidemic notification data released by the Hubei Health Commission, there were 52 cases in Suizhou, 47 in Jingzhou, 40 in Shiyan, 36 in Yellowstone, 36 in Xiangyang, 31 in Yichang, 25 in Enshi Tujia and Miao Autonomous Prefecture, 20 in Ezhou, 13 in Tianmen, 12 in Xiantao and 5 in Ezhou.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Data on outbound flights from Wuhan over the past period can also shed more light on where five million people went.

According to the flight attendants'statistics on the 12.30-1.22 departure capacity of Wuhan flights for domestic departure, international departure, Hong Kong, Macao and Taiwan, Beijing, Guangzhou, Chengdu, Haikou, Kunming, Xiamen, Shenzhen, Shanghai, Sanya, nanning is one of Wuhan's top 10 cities for outbound flights.

In terms of Hong Kong, Macao and Taiwan, Hong Kong is the largest destination for outbound flights from Wuhan, followed by Macao and Taiwan.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Internationally, the largest number of flights departing Wuhan is Bangkok, Thailand, the second is Singapore, the third is Tokyo, Japan.
